id: doc_refund_policy
type: doc
title: Refund policy for orders
text: |
  Refunds: Orders can be refunded only if status == 'paid' and refund requested within 30 days from created_at.
  Refund calculation: full refund minus processing fees. For multi-item orders, refund is per item if item-level return requested.
  Business rule: 'cancelled' orders have no refunds.

title: orders table
text:
Table: orders
Description: Stores customer purchase transactions.
Columns:
- id (int, primary key)
- customer_id (int, foreign key -> customers.id)
- total_amount (numeric) â€” total monetary value of the order.
- status (text) â€” order status; possible values: pending, paid, cancelled
- created_at (timestamp) â€” the order creation date (use this as the order date)
Relationships: orders.customer_id -> customers.id
Notes: Use created_at to filter orders by date ranges.
